      <div xml:id="NA83-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu iravukkuṟi vanta talaivaṉ (ET: talaimakaṉ) ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said while HE who had come to the night tryst was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA83">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            emmūr vāyi loṇṭuṟait taṭaiiya</l>
<l>            kaṭavuṇ mutumarat tuṭaṉuṟai paḻakiya</l>
<l>            tēyā vaḷaivāyt teṇkaṭ kūrukir</l>
<l>            vāyppaṟai yacāvum valimuntu kūkai</l>
<l>            maiyūṉ ṟerinta neyveṇ puḻukka </l>
<l>            lelivāṉ cūṭṭoṭu maliyap pēṇutu</l>
<l>            meñcāk koḷkaiyeṅ kātalar varanacaiit</l>
<l>            tuñcā talamarum poḻuti</l>
<l>            ṉañcuvarak kaṭuṅkural payiṟṟā tīmē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O strong [and] old(?)<note place="foot">Can <term xml:lang="ta">muntu</term> here mean more than just ‘old’?</note> owl whose drum of a mouth languishes,</l>
<l>[you with] sharp nail, clear eyes [and] untiring(?) curved beak,</l>
<l rend="indent">familiar for staying together in the plump god[-inhabited] old tree</l>
<l rend="indent3">by the bright ghat at the gate of our village,</l>
<l>we will honour you to [your] delight with a rat roasted white</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] a white boil of goat’s flesh [and] choice ghee</l>
<l>– don't use again [your] fierce voice for fears to come up</l>
<l rend="indent3">at a time when [she] is sleepless [and] agitated,</l>
<l rend="indent3">yearning for our lover of unswerving principles to come.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
